The paper deals with training deep neural networks and improving their performance, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also specifically mentions natural language processing and computer vision tasks, which are subfields of machine learning and computer science (cs.CV, cs.CL). The paper introduces a new regularization technique for training deep networks, which involves optimizing shared parameters, which is a common problem in deep learning (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions neural architecture search, which is a subfield of machine learning that involves finding the optimal architecture for a neural network (cs.NE).
